  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into discs</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624272039014-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624272039014-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624272039014-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624272039014-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624272039014-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato </strong>and<strong> courgette discs</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for an initial 15-20 min or until everything is starting to soften and brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624272042627-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624272042627-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624272042627-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624272042627-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624272042627-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>chives </strong>finely</p><p>Zest <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Combine your<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong> with the<strong> lemon zest</strong>,<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chopped chives</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>herby crumb</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624272046576-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624272046576-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624272046576-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624272046576-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624272046576-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything is starting to soften, add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>to the tray[s] over the veg</p><p>Squeeze the juice of <strong>half</strong> the <strong>lemon[s]</strong> over the chicken<strong> </strong>and top with the <strong>herby crumb</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a further 15 min</p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lemon</strong> into 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
